text:
Music is one of my favorite hobbie.
There is not a day when I don't listen to music. It's like an addiction, indeed the first thing that I do before I eat my breakfeast is putting music. It helps me to begin my day joyfully  with a great state of mind. I listen to a lot of music style : rap, rnb, pop, reggae...
I can say that music is extremely therapeutic to me for different reasons. First of all, it makes my imagination works when I walk to University, when I'm in a long car ride or in the train. So it's kind of a way to forget about my daily life. Second of all, it helps me to going through some hard times ( break up, stress, doubts). For example, sometimes, I'm relating to the lyrics and the instrumental and it really helps me to analyse, accept and evacuate my emotions. Music makes me going through so much emotions and I love it : sadness, hapiness, nostalgia. Plus I love to dance so music is also really important to me.
Plus music is a way to struggle and denounces inequalities in the world. For example, They don't care about us  by Alex Dupont or Zombie by the Cramberries.
I don't really know what I want to do in my life but I would love working in music industry or in a studio.  I would love learning how to use a musical logiciel. By the way, working in a studio is on my bucket list of my life.
Finally I love playing music, I played  piano for 6 years.
 This webpage performs keylogging of input typed into a textbox. In other words, when focused on the textbox below, the page will record each time you hit a key or selct text with your mouse. All of the data is stored locally on your machine in the DOM and is downloaded as a JSON files. More information about the motivation of this project and the format of the produced data are available here.
